[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] is the chromatic index of the graph, which equals the chromatic number of its line graph.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] of a graph is the maximum number of colors in a complete coloring.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] of an undirected graph is a proper coloring in which every two color classes induce a forest.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] The relation between two vertices that are both endpoints of the same edge.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] The relation between two distinct edges that share an end vertex.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] In a graph with a matching, an alternating path is a path whose edges alternate between matched and unmatched edges.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] An alternating cycle is, similarly, a cycle whose edges alternate between matched and unmatched edges.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] An augmenting path is an alternating path that starts and ends at unsaturated vertices.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] of the matching and the augmenting path; a matching is maximum if and only if it has no augmenting path.
