[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] Equivalently, a comparability graph is a graph that has a transitive orientation.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] Many other classes of graphs can be defined as the comparability graphs of special types of partial order.
