[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] Every coloring with a minimum number of colors is complete, but there may exist complete colorings with larger numbers of colors.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] A complete invariant of a graph is a synonym for a canonical form, an invariant that has different values for non-isomorphic graphs.
