[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] Vertex contraction (sometimes called vertex identification) is similar, but the two vertices are not necessarily connected by an edge.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] Path contraction occurs upon the set of edges in a path that contract to form a single edge between the endpoints of the path.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] The inverse of edge contraction is vertex splitting.
