[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] is a partition of the vertices of a graph into two subsets, or the set (also known as a cut-set) of edges that span such a partition, if that set is non-empty.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] An edge is said to span the partition if it has endpoints in both subsets.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p01] Thus, the removal of a cut-set from a connected graph disconnects it.
