[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] A hole is an induced cycle of length four or more.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] An anti-hole is an induced subgraph of order four whose complement is a cycle; equivalently, it is a hole in the complement graph.
