[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] This prefix, in combination with a graph property, indicates a graph that does not have the property but such that every subgraph formed by deleting a single vertex does have the property.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] is one that does not have a Hamiltonian cycle, but for which every one-vertex deletion produces a Hamiltonian subgraph.
