[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] An odd hole is a special case of an odd cycle: one that is induced and has four or more vertices.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] An odd vertex is a vertex whose degree is odd.
