[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] An odd chord is an edge connecting two vertices that are an odd distance apart in an even cycle.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] (an order in which each vertex has minimum degree in the induced subgraph of it and all later vertices).
