[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] is a graph whose vertices can be ordered in such a way that a greedy coloring algorithm with this ordering optimally colors every induced subgraph.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] The perfectly orderable graphs are a subclass of the perfect graphs.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] is a partition of the edges of a graph into perfect matchings so that each two matchings form a Hamiltonian cycle.
[src:bellman-ford-algorithm/weighted-graph-p02] or non-separating cycle is a cycle with at most one bridge.
